# Schemas — StructType vs DDL string

## Two ways, same result

- **Programmatic** — `StructType([StructField("amount", DecimalType(18,2)), ...])`
  - Verbose, explicit, easy to build from code
- **DDL string** — `"transaction_id STRING, amount DECIMAL(18,2)"`
  - Compact, SQL-flavored, easy to paste

## Always prefer explicit schemas in production

- **Inference triggers a full data scan** just to decide types — slow at scale
- It can **guess wrong** — e.g. a sparse `is_flagged` read as `string`, not `boolean`
